#### My kitty confg shortcut kitty_mod+a does not work because "ai" does not exist. Maybe the alias is not being loaded when laucnhing kitty? help pls  

To debug this issue, I'll need to see the following files:

1. `config/kitty/kitty.conf` - to check the keyboard shortcut configuration
2. `config/zsh/modules/aliases.sh` - to verify the 'ai' alias definition

Please add these files to the chat so I can help identify and fix the issue.

> Tokens: 3.6k sent, 70 received. Cost: $0.01 message, $0.01 session.  
> config/kitty/kitty.conf  
> Add file to the chat? (Y)es/(N)o/(A)ll/(S)kip all/(D)on't ask again [Yes]: y  
> config/zsh/modules/aliases.sh  
> Add file to the chat? (Y)es/(N)o/(A)ll/(S)kip all/(D)on't ask again [Yes]: y  

I see the issue. The problem is that kitty launches commands directly and doesn't process shell aliases. We need to modify the kitty configuration to use the full path to the `aider` command instead of relying on the alias.

Let's modify the kitty.conf file:

config/kitty/kitty.conf
```
<<<<<<< SEARCH
map kitty_mod+a		launch --type=window --cwd=current --location=hsplit ai
=======
map kitty_mod+a		launch --type=window --cwd=current --location=hsplit aider --no-gitignore
>>>>>>> REPLACE
```

This change replaces the `ai` alias with the actual command `aider --no-gitignore`. This should make the keyboard shortcut work properly since it no longer depends on shell aliases being loaded.

After applying this change, you'll need to restart kitty for the changes to take effect:

```bash
killall kitty
```

