#### helpme making the "ai" alias command run aider with colors being mostly white. i dont like the default green color that it uses  

To modify the "ai" alias color settings, I'll need to see the file where this alias is defined. Based on your repository structure, it's likely in:

`config/zsh/modules/aliases.sh`

Could you please add this file to the chat so I can help modify the aider color settings?

> Tokens: 3.6k sent, 62 received. Cost: $0.01 message, $0.01 session.  
> config/zsh/modules/aliases.sh  
> Add file to the chat? (Y)es/(N)o/(D)on't ask again [Yes]: y  

I'll help modify the aider alias to use white text instead of the default green. We can do this by setting the AIDER_STYLE environment variable.

Here's the change:

config/zsh/modules/aliases.sh
```bash
<<<<<<< SEARCH
alias ai="aider --no-commit --no-gitignore"
=======
alias ai='AIDER_STYLE="white" aider --no-commit --no-gitignore'
>>>>>>> REPLACE
```

This change will make aider use white text for its output. The AIDER_STYLE environment variable controls the color scheme, and setting it to "white" will give you a more neutral color scheme instead of the default green.

You can test the new alias by running:
```bash
source config/zsh/modules/aliases.sh
```

