#### how should I use the different chat modes?  

Aider has 3 main chat modes that you can switch between using commands:

1. /main (default) - Normal chat mode for discussing and editing code
2. /edit - Focused mode for just editing code, skips the chat responses
3. /chat - Conversation-only mode that won't edit any files

You can switch modes anytime with these commands. The current mode is shown in the prompt.

Some key points:
- /main is best for most work since it allows both discussion and edits
- /edit is good for rapid code changes without chat responses
- /chat lets you discuss code without risk of making changes

Relevant docs:
- https://aider.chat/docs/usage.html#chat-modes
- https://aider.chat/docs/commands.html

> Tokens: 1.5k sent, 159 received. Cost: $0.0068 message, $0.02 session.  

#### How do I enter into main mode  

You can enter main mode by simply typing:

```
/main
```

at the prompt. This is actually the default mode when you start aider, so you're probably already in it unless you switched to another mode.

You can always tell which mode you're in by looking at the prompt:
- `main>` for main mode
- `edit>` for edit mode 
- `chat>` for chat mode

Relevant docs:
- https://aider.chat/docs/usage.html#chat-modes

