#### Currently I use flags in the "ai" alias to run "aider" with specific configuration and colors. It seems there is a way of configuring aider via a file YAML. Migrate my configuration  

To migrate the aider configuration from command line flags to a YAML file, I'll need to:

1. See the current alias configuration from your zsh aliases file
2. Create a new aider config file

