I'll help migrate the aider configuration to a YAML file. First, let's create the config file and then update the alias to be simpler.

1. Create a new aider config file:

config/.config/aider/config.yml
```yaml
<<<<<<< SEARCH
=======
# Aider configuration
no_auto_commits: true
no_gitignore: true

# Color configuration
user_input_color: "#ffffff"
tool_error_color: "#ff9492"
tool_warning_color: "#f0b72f"
assistant_output_color: "#d9dee3"
>>>>>>> REPLACE
```

2. Update the alias to use the config file:

config/zsh/modules/aliases.sh
```bash
<<<<<<< SEARCH
alias ai='aider \
  --no-auto-commits \
  --no-gitignore \
  --user-input-color #ffffff \
  --tool-error-color #ff9492 \
  --tool-warning-color #f0b72f \
  --assistant-output-color #d9dee3'
=======
alias ai='aider'
>>>>>>> REPLACE
```

First, let's create the necessary directory:

```bash
mkdir -p config/.config/aider
```

The configuration will be automatically picked up by aider from the standard config location. The behavior should remain exactly the same, just managed through the config file instead of command line arguments.

