#### <blank>  

#### Great. I have a kitty theme that is setting the "active_tab_foreground" and "active_tab_background". I want to undo those colores the theme is applying, but without modifing the theme itself. I'm looking for away of saying: hey, please retore those values to the default ones that kitty would use  
#### .  

To override the theme's tab colors and restore them to kitty's defaults, we can explicitly set these values to "none" which tells kitty to use its built-in defaults. Here's how to do it:

config/kitty/kitty.conf
```
<<<<<<< SEARCH
# UI --------------------------------------------------------------------------

active_tab_font_style	regular

draw_minimal_borders	no

placement_strategy	top-left
=======
# UI --------------------------------------------------------------------------

active_tab_foreground   none
active_tab_background   none
active_tab_font_style	regular

draw_minimal_borders	no

placement_strategy	top-left
>>>>>>> REPLACE
```

This change adds the two lines to explicitly set both colors to "none", which will override any theme settings and restore kitty's default colors for active tabs. I placed them just before the existing active_tab_font_style setting since they're related tab appearance configurations.

The change will take effect after reloading the kitty config. You can reload it by either:
1. Using the keyboard shortcut Ctrl+Shift+F5 (or Cmd+Ctrl+, on macOS)
2. Or sending SIGUSR1 to kitty with:
```bash
kill -SIGUSR1 $KITTY_PID
```

