> kill -SIGUSR1 $KITTY_PID  
> Run shell command? (Y)es/(N)o/(D)on't ask again [Yes]: n  

#### 42:Invalid color name: 'none' in line: active_tab_foreground   none  

I see the error - we need to use the default kitty colors instead of "none". According to the kitty documentation, the defaults are:
- active_tab_foreground: #000
- active_tab_background: #eee

Here's the proper SEARCH/REPLACE block to fix this:

config/kitty/kitty.conf
```
<<<<<<< SEARCH
active_tab_foreground   none
active_tab_background   none
active_tab_font_style	regular
=======
active_tab_foreground   #000000
active_tab_background   #eeeeee
active_tab_font_style	regular
>>>>>>> REPLACE
```

This will restore the default kitty colors for active tabs, overriding any theme settings. The colors are specified in full 6-digit hex format for maximum compatibility.

After applying this change, you can reload the config with Ctrl+Shift+F5 (or Cmd+Ctrl+, on macOS) to see the effect.

